</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1464,2545,1225,1258]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="7.[1464,2671,716,1533]" box="[1464,2545,1225,1258]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1464,1699,1225,1258]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Goldman’s Spiny Pocket mouse is nocturnal and terrestrial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="200" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[1464,2671,716,1533]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1466,2161,1264,1297]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Goldman's Spiny Pocket Mouse has been observed living in pairs during the breeding season, and groups of six or more also have been reported sharing a burrow system while breeding.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="200" type="conservation">
